            <p>I kept noticing that the marketing that actually moved me wasn't marketing at all — it was someone being genuinely useful in a room full of the right people. A practitioner answering a question thoroughly, with no angle. A founder showing their work in a thread full of skeptics and winning them over by being straight with them.</p>
            <p>Kind Stranger is built to do that on purpose.</p>
